history.content: There remains significant waitlist capacity for 188 at present.  There are a small number of discussion sections that have full waitlists so you may need to pick a different discussion section to waitlist.  (If the waitlist is full at this point, it means it would have been unlikely waitlisting for that section would have resulted in you being able to enroll later through that section.)

I'm a freshman in LSCS, and I just submitted my declaration form. Based on the cs-advising email, I thought I would at least be put on the waitlist for CS188 (regardless of my standing/declaredness), but I received this error message:

Error: Request not processed. There is no wait list available. The wait list request was not processed, as there are no wait list places available for one or more of the class sections in this request.

Will the CS188 waitlist be extended sometime in the near future? I really want to take the class, and I would have enrolled earlier had my phase I appointment time been earlier.
history.subject: CS188 Waitlist
